The paper deals with the problem of recovering and completing matrices from Poisson observations, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the use of sparse vectors and compressed measurements, which are common in the field of data science (cs.DS).
